<subSubSection id="388144C4FFFAFFEF23CBFD2B3AFAFBE2" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7024174FFFFAFFEF23CBFD2B3CF4FCC5" blockId="1.[151,1437,647,1032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF23CBFD2B3963FD4A" bold="true" box="[151,287,647,672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Comments.</emphasis>
The species was described based on a single female and lacks any illustrations; so far it is known from only one taxonomic entry. The species was transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="B79B6CCCFFFAFFEF201CFD013BE7FD2E" authorityName="Westring" authorityYear="1851" box="[832,923,685,708]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF201CFD013BE7FD2E" box="[832,923,685,708]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Micaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="B79B6CCCFFFAFFEF20BAFD003D6BFD2E" authority="Simon, 1879" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1880" box="[998,1303,684,709]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micariolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF20BAFD003C09FD2F" box="[998,1141,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Micariolepis</emphasis>
Simon, 1879
</taxonomicName>
, due to the synonymisation of the two genera by 
<bibRefCitation id="140A6ABEFFFAFFEF2165FD633B6DFD02" author="Wunderlich" box="[569,785,719,744]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" refString="Wunderlich, J. (1980) Revision der europaischen Arten der Gattung Micaria Westring 1851, mit Anmerkungen zu den ubrigen palaarktischen Arten (Arachnida: Araneida: Gnaphosidae). Zoologische Beitrage, 25 (1979), 233 - 341." type="journal article" year="1980">Wunderlich (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="140A6ABEFFFAFFEF2047FD633BCAFD02" author="Simon" box="[795,950,719,744]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" refString="Simon, E. (1910) Arachnoidea. Araneae (ii). In: Schultze, L. (Ed.), Zoologische und anthropologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise im Westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika. Denkschriften der Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, 1910, pp. 175 - 218." type="journal article" year="1910">Simon (1910)</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<taxonomicName id="B79B6CCCFFFAFFEF276DFD7D3CD8FD02" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[1073,1188,719,744]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micariolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysis">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF276DFD7D3CD8FD02" box="[1073,1188,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. chrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="B79B6CCCFFFAFFEF27B8FD7D38A6FCE7" authority="Lucas, 1846" authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1846" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micariolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dives">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF27B8FD7D3D3FFD02" box="[1252,1347,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. dives</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="140A6ABEFFFAFFEF260DFD7C38AFFCE7" author="Lucas" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" refString="Lucas, H. (1846) Histoire naturelle des animaux articules. In: Exploration scientifique de l'Algerie pendant les annees 1840, 1841, 1842 publiee par ordre du Gouvernement et avec le concours d'une commission academique. Zoologie 1. Sciences physiques, Paris, 183 pp. [pp. 89 - 271]" type="book chapter" year="1846">Lucas, 1846</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a trans-Palaearctic species that clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B79B6CCCFFFAFFEF207AFD593BBCFCE7" authorityName="Tucker" authorityYear="1923" box="[806,960,756,781]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beaufortia">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF207AFD593BBCFCE7" box="[806,960,756,781]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. beaufortia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, redescribed below. In addition, these two African species differ in size, 
<taxonomicName id="B79B6CCCFFFAFFEF22BAFCB53A27FCDA" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[486,603,791,816]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micariolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysis">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF22BAFCB53A27FCDA" box="[486,603,791,816]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. chrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females being 
<quantity id="B763BAAAFFFAFFEF2059FCB43B3AFCC5" box="[773,838,792,816]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B79B6CCCFFFAFFEF2020FCB53C6AFCDA" authorityName="Tucker" authorityYear="1923" box="[892,1046,791,816]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beaufortia">
<emphasis id="42EFCB5DFFFAFFEF2020FCB53C6AFCDA" box="[892,1046,791,816]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. beaufortia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<quantity id="B763BAAAFFFAFFEF2741FCBB3CF8FCC5" box="[1053,1156,791,816]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" unit="mm" value="5.25">5.25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7024174FFFFAFFEF239BFC903AFAFBE2" blockId="1.[151,1437,647,1032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">
<materialsCitation id="C0F31D12FFFAFFEF239BFC903CC2FC77" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1576195183" county="Simon" location="Port Nolloth" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province" typeStatus="holotype">
The 
<typeStatus id="AF20A9EDFFFAFFEF23A0FC913950FCBF" box="[252,300,829,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">type</typeStatus>
locality of this species was indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="140A6ABEFFFAFFEF2053FC903BD1FCBE" author="Simon" box="[783,941,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" refString="Simon, E. (1910) Arachnoidea. Araneae (ii). In: Schultze, L. (Ed.), Zoologische und anthropologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise im Westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika. Denkschriften der Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, 1910, pp. 175 - 218." type="journal article" year="1910">
<collectingCounty id="99456FC3FFFAFFEF2053FC903B24FCBF" box="[783,856,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Simon</collectingCounty>
(1910)
</bibRefCitation>
as &quot; 
<collectingMunicipality id="90408D35FFFAFFEF20BDFC903CBDFCBF" box="[993,1217,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Petit Namaqualand</collectingMunicipality>
: 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF2793FC913D1FFCBF" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF2793FC913D1FFCBF" box="[1231,1379,828,853]" county="Simon" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Port Nolloth" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province">Port Nolloth</location>
&quot;; the country was not indicated. 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF2292FCF33A73FC92" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF2292FCF33A73FC92" box="[462,527,863,888]" county="Simon" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="There" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province">There</location>
are two names 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF219BFCF33B1BFC92" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF219BFCF33B1BFC92" box="[711,871,863,888]" county="Simon" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Namaqualand" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province">Namaqualand</location>
: one is 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF209DFCCC3CD8FC92" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF209DFCCC3CD8FC92" box="[961,1188,863,888]" county="Simon" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Great Namaqualand" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province">Great Namaqualand</location>
in 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF2797FCF33DE4FC92" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF2797FCF33DE4FC92" box="[1227,1432,863,888]" county="Simon" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="southern Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province">southern Namibia</location>
, and another is 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF221BFC283A56FC77" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF221BFC283A56FC77" box="[327,554,900,925]" county="Simon" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Little Namaqualand" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province">Little Namaqualand</location>
in north-western 
<collectingRegion id="B25FD9ADFFFAFFEF21A0FC283C64FC77" box="[764,1048,900,925]" country="South Africa" name="Northern Cape" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">
Northern 
<collectingRegion id="B25FD9ADFFFAFFEF2030FC283C64FC77" box="[876,1048,900,925]" inferredBySuffix="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Cape Province</collectingRegion>
</collectingRegion>
, 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF277AFC283CC2FC77" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF277AFC283CC2FC77" box="[1062,1214,900,925]" county="Simon" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="South Africa" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape Province">South Africa</location>
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation id="C0F31D12FFFAFFEF2790FC283AFEFBE2" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1576195182" country="Namibia" location="South Africa" municipality="Port Nolloth" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
The World Spider Catalog (2017) indicates its distribution as 
<collectingCountry id="088C57DFFFFAFFEF2122FC0B3A9DFC2A" box="[638,737,935,960]" name="Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Namibia</collectingCountry>
, although Little Namaqualand and 
<collectingMunicipality id="90408D35FFFAFFEF272CFC043C87FC2A" box="[1136,1275,935,960]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Port Nolloth</collectingMunicipality>
are located in 
<location id="75444194FFFAFFEF23CBFC60395BFC0F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFE523AFAFBE2:75444194FFFAFFEF23CBFC60395BFC0F" box="[151,295,972,997]" country="Namibia" municipality="Port Nolloth" name="South Africa" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">South Africa</location>
(
<figureCitation id="E8A00BCAFFFAFFEF2264FC6039F2FC0E" box="[312,398,972,997]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="7.[151,250,944,966]" captionTargetBox="[162,1418,195,922]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 30. Distribution records of Afrotropical Micaria: M. beaufortia (circle), M. chrysis (square) and M. tersissima (diamond)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832830/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). It seems that 
<bibRefCitation id="140A6ABEFFFAFFEF2166FC613A98FC0F" author="Roewer" box="[570,740,972,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1955) Katalog der Araneae von 1758 bis 1940, bzw. 1954. Fol. 2. Institut royal des sciences naturelles de Belgique, Bruxelles, 1751 pp." type="book" year="1955">Roewer (1955)</bibRefCitation>
assigned it to the wrong country, mentioning that the species was from &quot;SW-Afrika&quot; (currently 
<collectingCountry id="088C57DFFFFAFFEF2149FC433A07FBE2" box="[533,635,1007,1032]" name="Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Namibia</collectingCountry>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
